article.headline: Dubinsky's late 3-pointer lifts South Carolina State over Delaware State 66-64
article.description: — Wilson Dubinsky sank a 3-pointer at the buzzer, scoring 17 points and rallying South Carolina State to a 66-64 victory over Delaware State on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Dubinsky's late 3-pointer lifts South Carolina State over Delaware State 66-64
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- — Wilson Dubinsky sank a 3-pointer at the buzzer, scoring 17 points and rallying South Carolina State to a 66-64 victory over Delaware State on Saturday night. Dubinsky shot 6 for 8, including 5 for 7 from beyond the arc for the Bulldogs (6-14, 2-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Michael Teal and Jordan Simpson added eight points apiece. The Hornets (10-10, 3-1) were led in scoring by Deywilk Tavarez, who finished with 19 points. Jevin Muniz scored 16, while Martez Robinson added 11 points and six rebounds. Muniz had a layup with eight seconds remaining to give the Hornets a one-point lead. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
